    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="141"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 141.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Davis</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bancroft</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 228.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 30, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I transmit herewith a copy of a dispatch of this
                    date to Mr. Washburne, in answer to a telegram received from him yesterday,
                    which is embodied in the inclosure.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to ask that proper measures may be taken by the government of
                    North Germany for the protection of American property in Paris, in the event of
                    the occupation of that city by the German forces.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[This inclosure is embodied in Mr. Davis’s instructions to Mr. Washburne, No.
                        158, dated August 30, 1870. See, <hi rend="italic">ante,</hi> “France.”]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
